The paper discusses a mathematical formalization of the conceptual spaces framework, which is a way of representing knowledge. This is a topic that is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), computational linguistics (cs.CL), computational complexity (cs.CC), and information theory (cs.IT). Given the focus on measuring relations between concepts, cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.CL, cs.CC, and cs.IT.
